title: For Sale:  M1 Garand double-sized training rifle
postcontent: For sale is an M1 Garand double-sized training rifle. This large training aid was originally used by the military to teach the inner workings of the normal sized M1 Garand to new recruits. This is not a firing model and cannot be converted to fire ammunition. It measures 7ft. 2.5 in long and has a "US" Navy marking on the left side of the receiver. A brass plate with the manufacturer's name "National" is mounted inside the rifle. The operating rod, spring, bolt, and follower assembly all function just like the real version of the rifle when the action is cycled. The gas cylinder lock on the end of the barrel is removeable. There are several cutaway sections in the rifle to show how different parts operate. There is wear on the stock, which is also removeable and is held in place by three screws. The rifle is missing the trigger assembly, which is common with a military item of this age. These cutaway rifles are rare and don't come up for sale very often. This would make a great addition to anyone's military collection, man cave, or gun shop. It always draws a crowd and complete versions of these training rifles typically sell for around $1,500.00. I'm asking $500.00 OBO for the rifle as is. I can e-mail any additional pictures if needed. Thanks
